body.section:
         Namespaces in XQuery

While XSLT should serve to transform XML data into other (XML) formats, XQuery 
serves, for example, to select data from different sources on a NoSQL database,
harmonize them, and pass them on to processing workflows. |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .       
That is why it is not so surprising to me that the namespace concept in XQuery somehow works
better.

In order to be able to select data from an XML document with namespaces at all,
all namespaces must be specified at the beginning of the XQuery expression. This looks like this: |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .       xquery version "1.0-ml";

import module namespace tektur = "http://www.teturcms.de/xquery/common" 
                                  at "common.xqy";
import module namespace mem = "http://xqdev.com/in-mem-update" 
                                  at '/MarkLogic/appservices/utils/in-mem-update.xqy';
declare namespace local = "https://tekturcms.de/code/alex-sandbox/1.0";
declare namespace weiredns = "https://weired-ns-in-input-data.com/weired/ns";
declare namespace xs = "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"; 

Here, functions from other modules are first included. Those in a separate file common.xqy, as well as from the mem library in the MarkLogic
environment. Then a namespace local is declared for custom functions within the source file, as well as the namespace weiredns, which is present in the input data. The namespacexs is set analogously to the XSLT example. |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |  |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .           |   |                                                    Rejected by , .
